result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron G Behling was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Entry into/onto Bldg/Constuct.Site/Room, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.15(1).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Aaron G Behling in court with attorney Jeffrey A Schwarz.  Timothy J Cotter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court heard sentencing recommendations.
Additional statements made by defendant's grandmother, Janet K., and the defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to Count 2. Credit for 4 days time served. 
COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to Count 1. Credit for 0 days time served. 
COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2 (CONCURRENT TO EACH OTHER): 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation.
* No contact with the victim, Stein Garden Center.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety and submit to random urine screens.
* PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY restitution in the amount of $1,942.59 to the victim, Stein Garden Center - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* SERVE 90 days "condition time" - STAYED.  To be used by the Probation Department at its discretion for any violations or positive drug screens.

OTHER COURT ORDERS: 
* Court APPROVES transfer of this probation order to Shawano County.
  
Appeal rights given.

JusticePoint Pretrial Services "Violation" Report; received and filed.

Defendant Aaron G Behling in court with attorney Jeffrey A. Schwarz.  Timothy J. Cotter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form tendered to the Court.

Upon State's motion and pursuant to negotiations, Court AMENDS Count #1 to two misdemeanor charges.  Count #1 - Criminal Damage to Property [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 943.01(1)(a).  Count #2 - Entry Into a Locked Building [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 943.15(1)(a).

AS TO COUNT #1 & COUNT #2:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Parties request to adjourn the sentencing phase.
Court GRANTS request.
Case adjourned to 05-07-2014 at 1:30 PM - Br. 2, Judge Donald's Court for Sentencing Hearing.
